article.headline: Longwood 91, S. Virginia 82
article.story: FARMVILLE, Va. -- Ryan Bogan scored 23 points as the Longwood Lancers beat Southern Virginia 91-82 on Wednesday night. Bogan shot 8-for-13 for the Lancers (9-10), including 5-for-8 from 3-point territory. Durann Neil added 15 points, with all of his field goals coming on 3-pointers. The Knights (8-7) shot 57.1 percent from the field (32-for-56), but were outrebounded 40-21. In addition, they committed 23 turnovers as a team. The Lancers shot 13-for-30 from 3-point range (43.3 percent). They also dished out 22 assists as a team, with Dana Smith and E.J. Dawson totaling five apiece. Ade Swann led the Knights with 16 points. Cory Evans added 15, and Bryce Pendleton scored 14.
